Step 1 — Install Docker Desktop

Go to 👉 https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop
Click Download for Windows
Run the installer → when it asks "Enable WSL 2" → tick it → continue
After install, restart your PC
Open Docker Desktop → wait till you see "Engine running" (green dot bottom left)


Step 2 — Create Your Project Folder
Open File Explorer → go to C:\ → create a new folder called attendx
Inside attendx, create these subfolders:
C:\attendx\
├── backend\
├── frontend\
├── supabase\
└── docs\

Step 3 — Save All the Files
Download/save each file Claude gave you into the right folder:
FileSave tomain.pyC:\attendx\backend\main.pyrequirements.txtC:\attendx\backend\requirements.txtDockerfileC:\attendx\backend\Dockerfiledocker-compose.ymlC:\attendx\docker-compose.ymlnginx.confC:\attendx\nginx.conf.env.exampleC:\attendx\.env.exampleschema.sqlC:\attendx\supabase\schema.sqlattendance-system.htmlC:\attendx\frontend\index.html

⚠️ The HTML file must be renamed to index.html when you save it in the frontend folder


Step 4 — Setup Supabase (5 mins)

Go to 👉 https://supabase.com → Sign up free
Click New Project → name it attendx
Wait ~2 mins for it to load
Click SQL Editor on the left → paste the entire contents of schema.sql → click Run
Go to Settings → API → copy two things:

Project URL
service_role secret key




Step 5 — Create Your .env File

Open C:\attendx\.env.example in Notepad
Click File → Save As
Change filename to .env (just dot-env, no other name)
Change Save as type to All Files
Save it in C:\attendx\
Now edit .env in Notepad and fill in:

SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co   ← paste from Supabase
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=your-service-role-key          ← paste from Supabase
OFFICE_LAT=17.3850     ← your office GPS (Google Maps → right click → copy coords)
OFFICE_LON=78.4867
FENCE_RADIUS=500
FACE_THRESHOLD=0.42

Step 6 — Open Command Prompt
Press Windows key → type cmd → right-click → Run as Administrator
Navigate to your folder:
cmdcd C:\attendx

Step 7 — Launch AttendX 🚀
cmddocker compose up
```

**First time only** — this will download everything automatically (~1GB, takes 5–10 mins depending on internet speed). You'll see lots of text scrolling — that's normal.

When you see this, it's ready:
```
✔ Container attendx-api       Started
✔ Container attendx-frontend  Started

Step 8 — Open the App
Open your browser and go to:

🌐 http://localhost:3000 → AttendX web UI
🔧 http://localhost:8000/docs → API docs (to enroll employee faces)
❤️ http://localhost:8000/health → check backend is running


Daily Use (After First Setup)
Every morning to start:
cmdcd C:\attendx
docker compose up -d
To stop at end of day:
cmddocker compose down

If Something Goes Wrong
cmd# See error details
docker compose logs attendx-api

# Restart fresh
docker compose down
docker compose up

That's it! Want me to also walk you through the employee face enrollment step once it's running?
